A note on NonCommercial components
----------------------------------

A few annotated corpora carry NonCommercial terms: the PROIEL treebank, the
Universal Dependencies Perseus release, and the Gorman treebanks, plus
individual NonCommercial texts within GLAUx. What Dilemma extracts from
treebanks is factual form-to-lemma annotation and aggregate token statistics,
not the syntactic apparatus. Each source's license is recorded above, and for
GLAUx the license is recorded per text in its metadata, so NonCommercial
sources can be identified and excluded where a particular use requires it.
